Test README file

Simple compilation
==================

For a single core run just compile with

./configure
make 


Compilation on AIX Hitachi SR16000 machine
===================================================

Use the following lines
 
./configure --enable-mpi-hitachi CXX=mpCC -host=rs6000-ibm-aix CXXFLAGS="-I/srhome/scqcd/cossu/gsl/include -qlanglvl=stdc99" LDFLAGS="-L/srhome/scqcd/cossu/gsl/lib"
gmake

In order to override the default optimization level just add the 

"-qoptimize=#" 

option inside the CXXFLAGS (where # in between 1 - 5)

Use this line to compile on MPI general machine
===============================================
./configure --enable-mpi CXX=mpicxx.openmpi

Run with mpirun -np #nodes #executable

Testing and debugging
=====================
valgrind --leak-check=yes --log-file=valgrind.log ./hmc